# Day 21 – Route 53 DNS & Advanced NACL vs Security Group Troubleshooting

## Goal
Learn to diagnose DNS resolution and network access issues.

## Steps
- Verified Route 53 records and name servers.
- Tested DNS resolution using nslookup/dig.
- Checked NACL and Security Group rules.
- Adjusted inbound/outbound permissions.
- Confirmed connectivity restored.

## Lessons Learned
- Route 53 DNS issues often stem from record misconfiguration.
- NACLs are stateless; Security Groups are stateful.
- Always test from multiple subnets to confirm rule behavior.

